<%- include('partials/header', { title: 'The Experience' }) %>

<main>
  <!-- Experience Hero -->
  <section class="experience-hero section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>The Experience</h1>
      <div class="experience-intro">
        <p>Every journey is bespoke—crafted around your group's interests, energy, and sense of adventure. Whether you're drawn to coastal villages, vibrant cities, rural traditions, or the electric energy of Carnaval, we design an experience that feels like it was made for you. Because it was.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Details Grid -->
  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>The Details</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="details-grid">
        <div class="detail-card">
          <p class="label">Duration</p>
          <p class="value">6 Nights</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <p class="label">Group Size</p>
          <p class="value">4–12 Women</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <p class="label">Your Guides</p>
          <p class="value">1–2 of Us</p>
        </div>
        <div class="detail-card">
          <p class="label">Investment</p>
          <p class="value">From $2,500</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What It Might Look Like -->
  <section class="section section-sand">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What It Might Look Like</h2>
        <p>Every journey is different, but here's a sense of the experiences we might weave together:</p>
      </div>
      <div class="philosophy">
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <h3>Morning</h3>
          <p>Picture yourself waking to birdsong filtering through shutters, the morning air still cool and fragrant with jasmine. We might begin with a walk through a neighborhood market where vendors arrange pyramids of papaya and passion fruit, their hands moving with the practiced grace of ritual. A woman pressing tapioca at her griddle invites you to try, and suddenly you're learning the rhythm of her spatula, the exact moment when the edges curl golden. Or perhaps we'll follow a trail into the Atlantic Forest, where mist clings to the canopy and a local guide points out medicinal plants his grandmother taught him to recognize. These early hours belong to discovery, to the world before it fully wakes.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <h3>Afternoon</h3>
          <p>Afternoons unfold slowly, as they should. We gather at a long wooden table in someone's home or beneath the generous shade of a mango tree, where lunch becomes a three-hour conversation punctuated by laughter and the passing of dishes you've never tasted—moqueca fragrant with dendê oil, farofa that crumbles between your fingers, fresh coconut water drunk straight from the shell. A local musician might arrive with his cavaquinho, and songs emerge as naturally as the breeze. There's no schedule to keep, no next thing demanding your attention. Just the pleasure of sitting with new friends, of stories that meander and deepen, of tastes that linger on your tongue and in your memory.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <h3>Evening</h3>
          <p>As the light softens and turns golden, we follow the sound of drums to a roda de samba in someone's backyard, or perhaps to a small club where locals have been gathering for decades. The air grows thick with music and movement, with the particular electricity that happens when bodies respond to rhythm without thinking. You find yourself swaying, then stepping, then dancing in ways your body remembers but your mind had forgotten. A woman takes your hands and shows you the ginga, that subtle sway of hips that is both invitation and conversation. The night deepens around you, warm and alive, and you realize you've stopped being a visitor. These are the hours that stay with you: unscripted, unhurried, utterly alive.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What's Included -->
  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>What's Included</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="included-section">
        <div class="included-list">
          <h3>Your Investment Covers</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>6 nights of carefully selected accommodations</li>
            <li>All meals and drinks throughout your stay</li>
            <li>Internal transportation within Brazil</li>
            <li>All planned experiences and activities</li>
            <li>Your guide(s) with you throughout the journey</li>
            <li>Local connections and introductions</li>
            <li>Translation and cultural navigation</li>
            <li>Pre-trip planning and customization</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="included-list">
          <h3>Not Included</h3>
          <ul>
            <li>International flights to/from Brazil</li>
            <li>Travel insurance (required)</li>
            <li>Personal shopping and souvenirs</li>
            <li>Visa fees if applicable</li>
          </ul>
          <p style="margin-top: 2rem; color: var(--color-warm-gray); font-size: 0.95rem;">We're happy to advise on flight options and help with any logistics. Just ask.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Local Connections Image -->
  <section class="section section-white">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="experience-image-section">
        <img src="/images/RnLocals.png" alt="Making connections with locals in Brazil" class="experience-photo">
        <p class="image-caption">Making connections that last—strangers becoming friends on the streets of Brazil</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Who This Is For -->
  <section class="section section-sand">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header">
        <h2>Who This Is For</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="philosophy">
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <p>This experience is for women who want more than a vacation. It's for those who travel to be changed—who seek genuine connection over curated content, who are curious about other ways of being in the world.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <p>You might be gathering your closest friends for a milestone birthday. You might be part of a women's circle seeking an adventure together. You might be a solo traveler ready to join a group of kindred spirits.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="philosophy-item">
          <p><strong>Whoever you are, if you're reading this and feeling something stir—that's the invitation.</strong></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="section section-light">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="section-header" style="margin-bottom: 2rem;">
        <h2>Let's Begin</h2>
        <p>Tell us about your group and what draws you to Brazil. We'll take it from there.</p>
        <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-primary" style="margin-top: 2rem;">Start the Conversation</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</main>

<%- include('partials/footer') %>
